      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 178: After a shutdown timeout, the lambda may still be queued/running and captures `self`, keeping the instance alive while `terminate()` returns. That avoids stack use-after-free, but it means callers can observe destruction/shutdown as complete while cleanup is still pending. Prefer making timeout a hard failure path that still waits for actual cleanup completion, or document and guard the object lifecycle so no caller can proceed assuming NAT-PMP resources are closed.",
      "revId": "8a4e054d909bed55522cdbaa5cf5544055edad47",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
